Hospital Inpatient Discharges in New York: Diving into the Data related to Maternal Mortality

In this dataset, I’m exploring the discharge categories, particularly around pregnancy-related codes. From there, I’m looking at the racial and geographic breakdown of these diagnoses codes. This is a very priliminary exploration.

Explore Data: arrange, filter, and plot.

arranged_sparcs <- arrange(clean_sparcs, desc(ccs_diagnosis_code))

ectopic_pregnancies <- filter(clean_sparcs, ccs_diagnosis_code=="180")

Plot Ectopic Pregnancies by race

ggplot(ectopic_pregnancies, aes(factor(race), fill=race)) + geom_bar()

ggplot(ectopic_pregnancies, aes(factor(hospital_county), fill=race)) +  
  geom_bar() +
  coord_flip()

NOTE: Common risk factors of adverse birth–preeclampsia, eclampsia, abruptio placentae, placenta previa, and postpartum hemorrhag

Explore Hemorrhage during pregnancy (abruptio placenta; placenta previa) by County and Race

abruptio_placenta <- filter(clean_sparcs, ccs_diagnosis_code=="182")

ggplot(abruptio_placenta, aes(factor(age_group), fill=race)) +

Explore hyptertenion during pregnancy- NYC

hyptertension <- filter(clean_sparcs, ccs_diagnosis_code=="183") 


nyc_hypertension <- filter(clean_sparcs, ccs_diagnosis_code=="183" & hospital_county==c("Bronx", "Manhattan", "Richmond", "Kings", "Queens"))


ggplot(nyc_hypertension, aes(factor(hospital_county), fill=race)) +  
  geom_bar() +
  scale_fill_brewer(palette = "Set2", name = element_blank()) +
  labs(title = "Hyptertension Cases by Borough")

Pregnancy Related Complications in CCS Diagnosis Code

180 Ectopic pregnancy

181 Other complications of pregnancy

182 Hemorrhage during pregnancy; abruptio placenta; placenta previa

183 Hypertension complicating pregnancy; childbirth and the puerperium

184 Early or threatened labor

185 Prolonged pregnancy

186 Diabetes or abnormal glucose tolerance complicating pregnancy; childbirth; or the puerperium

187 Malposition; malpresentation

188 Fetopelvic disproportion; obstruction

189 Previous C-section

190 Fetal distress and abnormal forces of labor

191 Polyhydramnios and other problems of amniotic cavity

192 Umbilical cord complication

193 OB-related trauma to perineum and vulva

194 Forceps delivery

195 Other complications of birth; puerperium affecting management of mother

Filter for all pregnancy related complications

pregnancy_complications <- filter(clean_sparcs, ccs_diagnosis_code==c("183", "180", "181", "182", "184", "185", "186", "187", "188", "189", "190", "191", "192", "193", "194", "195"))

create barchart of of pregnancy related complications by type and race

ggplot(pregnancy_complications, aes(factor(race), fill=ccs_diagnosis_code)) +  
  geom_bar()

look at extreme risk to mortality for pregnancy complications

pregnancy_risk <- pregnancy_complications %>%
  filter(apr_risk_of_mortality=="Extreme") 

ggplot(pregnancy_risk, aes(factor(ccs_diagnosis_code), fill=race)) +  
  geom_bar()
